Healing, mana regen, agro control, damage dealing and of course buffing.<br>
Whilst most classes have a clearly defined role within this frame work druids do not.<br>
<br>
Healing<br>
=======<br>
CH and CH chains make druid healing more or less useless on a main tank once the chain is established.<br>
Also alot of heals are effectively negated by a subsequent CH and consequently a watse of mana.<br>
With the damage output of mobs these days once someone has agro on a nasty mob there is no way a druid alone can keep them alive.<br>
AE damage can be healed by a druid but without a group heal, bad players or a player on low HP people will die and a large mana pool is needed to heal effectively.<br>
Druids do heal on raids however I dont think any one could seriously define a druids role on a raid as a healing one.<br>
<br>
Mana regen<br>
==========<br>
This is mainly done (in fight) via mages mod rods. It could also be done by necros mana dumping but necros seem rather scarce on raids these days.<br>
Indeed sometimes a druids role is to heal clerics that are mod rodding.<br>
<br>
Agro control<br>
==========<br>
Druids have no spell or skill to control their own agro let alone anyone elses.<br>
<br>
Damage dealing<br>
==============<br>
Druids have some reasonable nukes. But again the disparity between the damage druids and other classes can do means that you could not reasonably say a druids role on a raid was a damage dealing one.<br>
<br>
Buffing<br>
======<br>
Druids do not buff in most groups let alone a raid.<br>
<br>
Conclusion<br>
=========<br>
Give druids the abiltity to mana dump like necros (incidentally i think chanters should get this ability too, to give them something to do other than buffing).<br>
Let the clerics heal but let druids give them the mana to do it.<br>
Let the wizards blast and again let druids give them the mana to do it.<br>
Let shaman/clerics/chanters buff but rather than a druid sitting there FOM waiting for the buffing to finish let them help out by supplying other classes with mana.<br>
<br>
There is a certain school of thought that flowing thought items are a waste for a druid and would be better suited to a cleric or a wizard because they get more value for their mana. Indeed a druid has to fight hard for loot these days.<br>
<br>
The ability for a druid to mana dump would make them a viable, needed and (dare I say it) wanted class on a raid.<br>
There is very little druids can do with their mana so why not let us give it to other classes. <br>
<br>
<br>
